Solar eclipses that occur when the moon obscures the sun twice each
year are eagerly viewed by thousands when they affect a populated
area.  Some ancient peoples and even some moderns fear an eclipse.
The greatest danger for people is potential eye damage from looking
directly at the sun.</SUM>
